      <hedline>
        <hl1>THE MARKETS: CURRENCIES</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Japanese yen drops after Bank of Japan leaves interest rates unchanged, saying economy might not be ready for higher borrowing costs; in New York, dollar settles at 108.12 yen, up from 107.87; graph; chart (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>THE YEN FALLS. The yen dropped after the Bank of Japan left interest rates unchanged, saying the economy might not be ready for higher borrowing costs. In New York, the dollar settled at 108.12 yen, up from 107.87.</p>
      </block>
